We proceed as follows:

1. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
 • Average Accounts Receivable = (Beginning AR + Ending AR) / 2 = (0 + 200359.99) / 2 = 100179.995  
 • Ratio = Main Business Revenue / Average AR = 547392.30 / 100179.995 ≈ 5.47  

2. Operating cash flow ratio  
 • This ratio is defined as Operating Cash Flow divided by Total Current Liabilities  
 • Ratio = (–2868695.86) / 5042389.63 ≈ –0.57  

3. Operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio  
 • In our example this has the same definition as the above  
 • Ratio = –2868695.86 / 5042389.63 ≈ –0.57  

4. Total Asset Turnover Ratio  
 • Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2 = (16000000 + 21098887.48) / 2 = 18549443.74  
 • Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets = 547392.30 / 18549443.74 ≈ 0.03  

5. Debt to Equity Ratio  
 • Total Debt is taken as the Total Current Liabilities (there are no non-current liabilities provided) = 5042389.63  
 • Total Owner's Equity = 16056497.85  
 • Ratio = 5042389.63 / 16056497.85 ≈ 0.31  

Therefore, the final solution in the required JSON format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "5.47",
    "operating cash flow ratio": "-0.57",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-0.57",
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.03",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.31"
  }
}
